caption: HIDDEN GEM!! A little hidden gem in FIDi serving up smiles & fresh delicious breakfasts. You can taste the difference with cage free eggs. 8 grain toast was divine. Cafe Au Lait rounded out our Sunday breakfast perfectly. The staff were friendly & attentive!
The best place for breakfast in the neighborhood. Vegan cacao waffle with smashed avocado my favorite.

Honestly so unimpressed. I paid $4.00 for a side of bacon and I got three of the thinnest (not even crispy) slices of bacon I've ever seen in my life. Like, almost see-through. They're charging $1.33 per slice for the most pathetic bacon I've ever been served!  We also ordered a classic waffle and a gluten-free waffle. Neither were good. The classic waffle is so hard it tore up my gums after eating only one quarter if it. The gluten-free waffle was actually better than the regular, but there was just no flavor. And both were super dry. Even our Mocha smoothie is pretty flavorless! I had to take a bite of something else just to check that I don't have covid or something!  The chai is nice, however. Lightly sweet, which is perfect for us. And the banana bread has great flavor, and is spiced so nicely. But also really, really dry.  We definitely won't be ordering here again, which is so disappointing. It's hard to find healthy, gluten-free free food that also tastes good. And I guess we're still on the hunt!
Average coffee
Cute cafe in FiDi. Keto/paleo/vegan options. Made to order brunch-all day. Great coffee!
Excellent! Get there early (before 9) to avoid a line. Had the grilled corn bread with jalapeño jelly - perfect hint of spice. Jelly was very sweet even with jalapeños. Very shareable portions!
Favorite takeout coffee and breakfast place, really like the Down Under Truffle Smash.
Great coffee ;)  and the owner is a real professional, really knows her business.
I liked the kind service. It was great. A cup of tea and an 🥑 sandwich made my wet Monday.
Coffee
Love this cafe. And besides the very good coffeevand Matcha.Is the people working there . Always wonderful. I think the  barista name is Rafael he is WONDERFUL. M
Absolutely beautiful design, minimalistic approach makes it attractive in a very different way. Love the menu with many healthy option.
Its ok

I ordered the “Avo Smash” and thought it was served on a waffle, but it was served on toast. The waffle version is called the “Cacao Waffle Avo Smash,” so make sure you’re descriptive when you place your order. Either way, what I had was excellent, light and refreshing.  There’s great people watching from the barstool seating along the window. But it’s important to note there isn’t very much seating in the restaurant overall.

I have never had a bad item from this menu.  The drinks are delightful and the food is even better.  The avocado toast is THE BEST I have had anywhere in NYC.  I ordered online yesterday for pick up and mentioned that I am pregnant and cannot have the goat cheese.  One of the associates working there called me directly to say she also had children and can assure me the goat cheese is made from pasteurized milk and is safe to eat.  I thought this was so nice of her to take that step, she went above and beyond.  And the avocado toast (and tomato toast) is SOOO great.  The mashed avocado is superb with peas and microgreens and the creamy goat cheese and they give a slice of lemon for a dash of acidity...and it's the perfect size and fills you up...I highly recommend this place, the staff is so friendly and the place is modern and clean.  Thanks Boundless Plains!
Amazing coffee! Delicious waffles and snacks! Super friendly staff!!
Love my coffee here. Melbs standards 👌👌👌

“Bravo” to this charming little Aussie-style woman-owned coffee shop on Rector St. I came in today for a coffee and to catch up with several guys for a regular Monday noon meeting down in FiDi. Lovely and luminous space, delicious coffee, excellent food, impeccable and courteous service, comfortable tables well spaced apart, and the fact that you the owner is actually there interacting with customers makes it feel authentic. This is my new go-to café in FiDi.

I recently had an absolutely delicious espresso there. A few hours later, I returned, inquired about the coffee used (a single-origin variety from Rwanda), and happily purchased a bag of beans from them. What a treat! It’s perhaps the only interesting coffee shop in a neighborhood filled with chains. Highly recommended.
Level much lover than price, my guess its ok for location  , also you should love loud club music because it is , never again
Hidden gem! Upscale coffee shop with hot food. They have amazing chai latte and avocado toast. Beware: it is pricey. Breakfast for two was $42. Walk by Dunkin’s and perch here!

Not going to lie,  coffee was straight up sour and I overheard the women next to me say the same thing. Probably just the barista at the time was too inexperienced. Coffee and meal were also quite expensive, I recommend Bluestone Cafe for a better, cheaper alternative nearby.
We didn't feel well after dining here. The salad didn't look and taste fresh.
Great spot for a coffee/tea while getting some  work done. Food is good and staff welcoming
The food was alright, I wouldn’t say I loved it but the service was amazing. The servers were fun & friendly & definitely made me smile.

I rated it half because the waffles that I ordered were bitter and bland and the hot chocolate didnt even taste like chocolate. But the service and the people working there were very happy and delightful.
This place is great!! had breakfest with my children and they loved the waffles!!! Employees where amazing, music and vibe of this place is awesome!! Loved it
Friendly staff, amazing coffee, and some Aussie-inspired food. Worth walking past other cafes to try this one. I met the owner, Anna, who came out to say hi when she recognized my Australian accent.
(Translated by Google) Coffee tastes good. Flat white is highly recommended :)  (Original) 커피 맛이 좋아요. 플랫 화이트 강력 추천합니다:)
Clean and cute place I got flat white so good!

I didn’t even get the food from this place. Food was ordered online and they left a voice mail saying there’s no ingredients left and they would cancel the order after 45 mins since they received my order. They should update earlier if they knew that they were running out of the ingredients.
Yummy avo toast
Great coffee haven't had anything else yet but I am sure if the coffee is good then their food is good as well .
Small breakfast and coffee spot. A few tables and some bench seating. Great breakfast food (avocado waffles, egg wrap) and good coffee for a fair price. No complaints.
Can’t be missed on a Sunday morning.
Wonderful all around. Boundless Plains has great staff, excellent espresso drinks and food, and the best cold brew I've had anywhere.
Good coffee and pastries, and a small business owner that cares.  Skip Starbucks and Dunkin Donuts and support a local shop!
What a pleasant surprise to find this cafe and have a chat with the owner who is a fellow Australian, great coffee,  yummy pecan and cranberry biscuits, thanks!!
Great coffee and partiers, friendly service!
Friendly service, top notch espresso, attention to detail in every bite - and every nook and cranny Of the cafe! Cozy & delectable; well worth a stop!
Awesome addition to the neighborhood! Excellent cappuccino! They use Counter Culture Coffee. Great vibe with plenty seating. Friendly staff, amazing owner :) thanks Jo
The guy working was incredibly friendly and helpful. The vanilla latte I ordered was delicious and so was the classic waffle! Definitely would recommend.
I pop in here all the time for a flat white or a cortado. Great coffee, quick bites,  and fantastic atmosphere.
Great flat whites

This is my favorite coffee shop in the neighborhood. The owner is working behind the bar and really cares about all aspects of her shop. Her hard work pays off.  The espresso is rich, the breakfast bowl is something I would strive to make at home and the whole place gives off wellness vibes.
The avocado smash was good...but the dark choc waffle was very disappointing

Walked into the shop and the 2 guys making the coffee are arguing about being superficial to customers, one of then finally has enough and walks away after taking my order. Once my order is ready the guy calls out for 2 espresso I ordered a flat whit and espresso.  I tell him and he exclaims "basically the same thing" so I think ok what ever I'll drink it anyways. Coffee straight up taste like ash trey.

This place is great. The coffee is great. Jo (and the other staff whose names I can't remember) are all lovely, and Jo really cares about making sure people are having a good experience, feel cared for, etc. Totally recommend going here!!
This place is excellent. Great Australian cafe style coffee. The best I found in NYC!
Glad to have found proper coffee in NY

If you are looking for a proper flat white, an authentic avo on toast (with Meredith goats cheese and wedge of lemon), and a delightful host - Boundless Plains is your place. Jo has managed to carve out a perfect little slice of home here for any Australians and Kiwis searching for a good brew. Try the tomato on toast too - good chutney, fresh tomato and whipped ricotta. Do yourselves a favour and visit.

I wanted to like this more but, disappointingly, was let down by some easily fixable aspects. Aussie coffee shops are, thankfully, springing up fast across NYC so there is plenty of competition. Wattle offers some tasty brunch options and well made coffee (plus Milo for the true taste of Aus). The downside was the staff were not at all engaging and basically monosyllabic; maybe because the place was roasting hot (I assume the aircon was not working). In their defence they were also overstretched because there were only three of them in total, which just wasn’t enough. We saw plenty of mixed up orders and customers chasing forgotten orders. Hopefully this can be turned around because it’s a nicely decorated, bright location with good food and coffee.
Great place to stop for drinks or food. The owner Jo was lovely, really welcoming! Such a great chilled out atmosphere. Would definitely recommend!
The espresso brought me back...
Great coffee, great avocado toast, great tomato toast. Has Meredith goat’s cheese! for that authentic touch. Oh, and great service too.
Great coffee in a soulless neighborhood
Good coffee and friendly staff.
I liked the decor. Presentation of food was good. Amazing services. Great food menu. I liked the coffee.

Great coffee, nice place, good music, terrible service. Waited half an hour for an espresso and for some reason, the waiter (maybe the owner?) was giving us attitude. Four costumers who came later than us got served sooner. Not coming back :)
Stumbled onto this great little spot randomly! Delicious baked goods and really smooth coffee. deceptively big inside if you want to hang out! Would definitely recommend.

I have had a couple of great cappuccinos here in the past but what was served up this morning was super disappointing given the $4.25 price tag. It just didn’t taste right and was topped with roadhouse foam. We took it back thinking maybe there was just a newbie on the counter making them but were told that’s what a cappuccino looks like here.
Great little coffee spot that is super chill with a great atmosphere. Fantastic coffee and awesome food. They keep the menu simple with seasonal specials - perfect. ☕️ 😋

Love the ambience and color scheme of this place! The white gives out a peaceful lively vibe. The music is also upbeat. They have wifi, enough seating, and a restroom which makes it a great place to work out of. It is a short walk from the 9/11 memorial or WTC as well as the wall street charging bull making it a nice hideout spot amidst the busy Financial District. I tried their oat mocha - strong and delicious! Would come here again to work and try their food/bakery items.

Quaint little cafe with bright yellow coffee cups like the silver wattle where it gets its name. The staff is so friendly and food delicious. They make vegan taste good :)  if i lived in thus neighborhood i’d eat here all the time.

Yeah. Coffee’s fine. Has a peaceful ambience but destroyed by the bad, LOUD music selection. I’m just trying to have coffee, do some work, and relax. Not trying to attend a music concert. I’ll go to Brooklyn for that.
Food is very tasty and nice drinks.  Staff don’t interact too much but are nice enough.
Coffee is delicious. The location is very nice and clean and peaceful i can come and study and i know i wont be disturbed. I will return to grab a coffee and study some more.

Popped in to get a bit of last minute studying done and have some food. I was pleasantly surprised with the quality of food. I had the beet and citrus salad with a poached egg. It was well worth the price. And it was beautiful on top of tasting amazing. Also one of the best flat whites I’ve had in a long time. I don’t write reviews often, but this little place has good quality food in FiDi!
Good milk alternatives for lattes. Fast service cute aesthetic
The owner, Jo, is SO RUDE! Will never support a place with a monster as the owner.

Small place with a friendly and welcoming vibe. Coffee was delicious, but I was disappointed with my waffle. It was over cooked and the toppings were minimal. Maple syrup coats extra but even that didn’t salvage the waffle.
Great Coffee but do NOT get their smoothies! Yuck

I ordered delivery this morning for breakfast. The waffle is missing all the things it's supposed to come with. The waffle is VERY COLD AND HARD and tough to eat. I paid $1.50 extra for strawberries and received 4 strawberries. I paid 2.00 extra for syrup which was so small it only covered 1 half of the waffle with a light pour.  This food was awful. I was missing everything and it was way over priced. I will never eat or order from here again.
Excellent espresso, very knowledgeable and friendly staff, highly recommended
The chicken avocado sandwich is good!
Great coffee, nice people
Cute little place. Good coffee and overnight oats
The pizza is soooooo good

Great espresso drinks and excellent breakfast options. I've been looking for a new go-to coffee place in FiDi and have to say this is some of the best coffee I've had in NYC. Unlike some other coffee shops, the food is as good as the coffee. Breakfast bowls and avocado toast were amazing and great-looking pastries too.  Expect to wait a bit for made-to-order food (as opposed to pastry), but it's worth it.
Very cute and tasty cafe.
Found this place while exploring NYC and the 9/11 memorial. Great coffee
Free coffee on the crave app!

Excellent cortado!  Tried a couple of coffee shops in the area and haven't been impressed with their espresso, but this was great.  Also tried the avocado toast with a poached egg (pretty pricey at $17, but I guess that's par for the course these days).  Food came out before the coffee (even though there were only 2 drinks ahead of me)...so maybe not the place to swing by if you're in a hurry for your coffee. Stopped in on a weekday around 10AM and plenty of spots to grab a table.  Music was a bit loud, but I was just there to get some work done, so that was fine.  Will be back!
Simply delicious.  The food is well seasoned and fresh.  This is a place for comfort food.  I plan to come back and try all the other items there.

my boyfriend and i were in the mood for some waffles and picked this place because it seemed cute. we were totally surprised by all their different waffle menu options and decided to try the cacao avo smash. that was the best decision of my life. i think the only words that came out of my mouth the entire visit were “this is... so good..” over and over. it was so good. and we got eggies that were... So .. Good.. you could tell the food was made with love and the staff was soo kind. 11/10. going back to nyc just for wattles!!
Overpriced, careless service

We were excited to try this cafe, as we'd only found bad coffee in NY during our vacation  When we told the lady behind the counter this, she got super defensive and told us that we could get great coffee everywhere. Odd reaction. The coffee was Ok. The milk was super hot in the flat whites resulting in a poor texture, and the coffee was spilt everywhere in the saucer when it was delivered. We'll not be back - mainly due to the bad attitude of the one staff member. A smile would make all the difference - no need to stand with crossed arms looking miserable at customers. I felt sorry for the guy working alongside her.
Interesting ideas, but the waffles were bland and mushy.
Just ok
It's trying to be an Australian cafe but it's not really working.
(Translated by Google) The Overnight Oats are heavenly  (Original) Die Overnight Oats sind himmlisch
Small but potent cups of espresso, and delightful staff. The space is pretty limited, (getting a group past the order line is a hassle), but the experience is worth it.
Awesome coffee. Fast service and friendly people. I liked this experience. Birch was closer to us. But this is definitely worth a recommendation.

Coming from a Colombian background and after living in Brazil for two years on my own, I personally found the coffee from this shop to be too weak for my personal taste. I needed something to wake me up - and the coffee here tasted more like water, or milk really, than anything else. Nice space inside and kind baristas, but the service was too slow. I had to wait more than five minutes to get my flat white and there was only one couple ahead of me. I'm looking for a coffee shop to frequent daily in the area. This won't be it.

$20 chocolate waffle with two eggs, two bacon, and a large coffee.  Considering that waffle is their specialty, it was really dry and nothing special.  You order at the counter and the staffs seems like they don't care.  I asked for scrambled eggs and they gave me fried eggs.  They forgot strawberries and when I asked about it, one of the staff gave me an annoyed look.  Ended up with one strawberry, sliced into 4 pieces...  Not worth the price.  At least the coffee was good.
Nice waffles
Great cafe with awesome lattes...and sandwiches

Australian themed - Clean and nicely decorated. Great selection of healthy foods, chia bowl, etc.  The Yellow smoothie was great and the croissant was the best I've ever tasted, so fresh.  Seems family owned, staff is quiet and attentive, chill music, positive vibes.  I must go back and try the Beach & Dessert waffle at Wattle.
The best espresso in the financial district. Nice cookies and good prices.
Great sugar free food and amazing coffee!
4 stars is for the free WiFi, comfortable place to sit and work, and the friendly staff. The coffee was good, the avocado toast was mediocre and felt very overpriced.
I was society, next time if there any waffles I may get strawberry syrup

Best coffee shop in fidi. I love the atmosphere and the coffee. I usually get a capucino and an almond pastry but everything I've tried has been delicious. The matcha is one of the best ever. I go here in the morning before work or for a break when work is stressful and I need to clear my mind.
Always great coffee. The cafe has a nice modern feel too. Never tried any food there but the menu looks good.
Ordered from their catering menu - it was so delicious and everyone gave the sandwiches and waffles a big thumbs up. Thanks so much!
Nice little corner for coffee. Swag teas, and smooth Parlor Coffee espresso drinks
Very good and more than enough!
Great beverages, prepared very carefully by the staff, and lots of really delicious, clean food choices.

Food is great. I order here on seamless for breakfast, their truffle eggs and avocado toast are incredible. Food is simply delicious. Their 5 star reviews are all on point, the food is properly gourmet.
I loved the coffe, awesome
Everything is nice inside wattle. And those charcoal waffles are delicious!
Fine I guess. Flat and white. It might be your thing
Yum Keto
Great place.  Great food. Great coffee.  The sweet treats omg. people too. I will visit alone or with friends.

Good espresso spot in lower Manhattan. All white, sleek interior. Great coffee beans. Espresso and filter coffee.  Had a vegan ginger molasses cookie that was really tasty. Rest of pastries looked good, too.

This place is Clean, beautiful and has amazing food. It is one if my favorite places in Murray Hill. The Egg Salad Sandwich is extremely yummy. I order from them literally every day on Grubhub. Also if you guys love scrambled eggs or omelettes, then come here! Its very fresh. They also have yummy waffles and Granola. Ugh, I could go on and on about how yummy this place is.
I love this place more than any coffee shop in NYC
Really delicious coffee. New favorite spot for espresso drinks in the neighborhood.
The place is very chic and modern. I ordered a  latte and cranberry loaf really good! The customer service was excellent!
Love it, cozy, great amicable atmosphere. Great quality service. Love the coffee, almond crossaint was perfect great
Nice small place. Espresso was good but in a paper cup. Was able to find a seat at 4 PM no problem
Was so eager to try as a new place to get work done with some wonderful coffee, but... No wifi

very cute and nice place. i really enjoy the atmosphere there especially in the afternoon when i can find myself in peace on one of spots next to the window with my favourite coffee. add it to your go to list
(Translated by Google) It was delicious.  (Original) 美味しかったです。
Very good avocado toast!
This is a cute little local place.  The food is quite good.  The service is a little disorganized, but it's a nice place to go for brunch.

Updated review— I came back for a regular latte but no latte art this time. The place was empty so no reason for it. It looked just like a cup of coffee. I was a bit disappointed but it tasted ok. They have few tables and portable air conditioner  Prior review— Nice and friendly service. Cafe is clean with cute decor. I ordered a latte. It was beautifully presented and the barista brought it to our table. Latte was delicious and served in a cute yellow mug.

Two and a half weeks after we left the boundless plains of Australia for the USA we’ve finally found a good coffee!!! Thank you for bringing decent coffee to this land of the burnt brown liquid. As for the reviewer who didn’t like it and only went because Dunkin Donuts was closed ... their usual choice of cafe says it all! Keep sharing the good stuff from the land girt by sea!!
Cute little place with good toast and tea/coffee

Good coffee, but the overnight oat was just ok. It was cold and the ingredients were not mixed together. Same for the banana bread, all the ingredients were served closed to each other but not mixed in an actual recipe.

This is one of my favorite places in all of NYC! Once inside, I feel like I’ve left the city and gone into a very quaint coffee shop, far far away. The service is excellent, the people are so friendly and kind, the food is DIVINE and looks like it came straight out of Bon Appetit Magazine (their avocado toast is the best!), the hot beverages are delicious, the decor is so simple yet so perfect, everything about this place makes me happy!
Great coffee, relaxed atmosphere, quiet. Closed at 3pm on Saturday though :O
Great breakfast. The eggs were so fluffy and yummy and the chia bowl was also very good.
Everything here was made fresh and so good!!
Very nice Aussie Café serving a pretty good Flat White and great matcha waffles and Avocado on toast. The place is a bit small but we always found a good seat.
I have not had as delicious a chai latte since visiting Australia years ago.  The food is also yummy and healthy.  So happy to know about this neighborhood gem.
Australian cafe,  bright setup. Great juices. The waffle was a bit dry but otherwise ok.
Love this place since day one! Great coffee, nice vibe, friendly staff.  Very very good matcha latte!

The interior was nice but that's about it. Customer service was mediocre. But it's the coffee. It is soooo baaaaad!!!!! It made me gag. It was awful. The only reason I went there was because the dunkin donuts next door had a long line.
Best coffee in NYC, of course an Australian owns it!
Absolutely love this place. One of my favorite cafes in NYC
The place is awesome. Gluten-free taste with a avocado was big-enough and delicious. Service is also good. Photo of my decaf almond milk late :)

I had the salmon and avocado mash on waffles. Awesome! Don't forget to close the door on your way in/out. I tipped the counter guy an extra dollar just for closing the door twenty-ish times over the course of my meal. All in all I had a great breakfast here!
Very clean place.  Had the iced mocha which was okay.

Found this great indy cafe right across from my hotel.  Espresso drinks are exceptional - very intense without the 'charred' notes of another famous coffee.  Friendly staff.  I hope they do well as they'll figure prominently in my choice of hotel next visit - yes, that good.
Great coffee!

Finally a place that doesn't overcook their eggs!  & Gluten free too!  Been once, will re-review after a few visits  Edit:. After a couple of visits, I'm going to double down here.  Very tasty, reasonably priced, clean, and super friendly/ nice staff.  Pretty sure they get all their food locally.  Again, perfectly cooked eggs and gluten free substitutions available.  Can't go wrong
Best coffee in NY. Excellent service. Thanks!
A great little cafe near the World Trade centre memorial. Coffee and food are top notch.
Found this little shop toe years ago and have been coming back ever since.  The staff is friendly and the atmosphere is chill. The have good coffee too.
Great menu and treats, bright clean space to hang out for a bit.  Fave coffee spot near Battery park.
Great aesthetic, friendly staff, delicious food

First time ever.  1. The atmosphere is comfortable, clean and just nice.  I loved it.  2. The food was wonderful.  I am not a waffles fan, but I really enjoyed the scrambled eggs and waffles. 3. The matcha latte was no joke.  It was the real deal.  The beverages are true blue.  Also they serve Milo!

The perfect  place to enjoy a cup of coffee wirh either self made yummy pastries, healthy sandwiches and much more. Very friendly personnel. The Holiday Inn Hotel Manhattan Financial District is also just opposite across the road. We will definitely come back for more of that delicious coffee and pastries.
Nice, gentle and very good coffee.
If you're looking for a fresh and healthy breakfast that'll kick-start your day, look no further. The personnel is genuinely friendly the service is good and the food even better.
No taste mocha. Bad steamed milk in latte.
Amazing!
Quaint little place with great food and very friendly staff, love it there!!!

Best coffee in Fidi and some amaaaazing toasts. Lady who works behind the counter is super friendly and welcoming. So happy to have this place near my work!
Good coffee and snacks
Excellent little coffee ☕ shop with seating for about 12. Very good coffee, espresso drinks and friendly service. Hard to notice from the street but worth a visit.
Excellent espresso based drinks and some overpriced but tasty breakfast options. Definitely my go to in FiDi
Really great Chai and friendly staff.

Great vibe, excellent coffee!!! The hospitality of the staff made the difference compared to other coffee shops in the city. Here I felt like a friend more than a customer.  Definitely worth the visit. Hopefully, they can expand around the city.

This was my first time placing an order with this place. I called on the phone and I said can I place an order for delivery please? The gentelmen that I spoke to said yes  and put me on hold for 7 minutes. I hung up and I called back and I said I've been on hold for a long time and just wanted to place an order for delivery he then took my order and asked me how am I going to pay and I said "I will pay cash" he said "Cash. Okay you're all set." Before he hang up I asked "How much is the total just so I have the caSH PREPARED." He told me how much I had to pay and we hangup. I waited for my order more than an hour and then I called to ask where my order was at and this lady on the phone says "Your food left already" then I said "It's not here so I don't know where it went. Then she asked for my name an put me on hold and said she was gonna talk to the manager. The Manager then told her "We don't take cash for deliveries it's only by card.". After all this time of waiting for my food she tells me that when it was already confirmed. Don't buy from this place. This people are rude and don't respect costumers. The worst expirence I've had ordering food so far.
A brilliant coffee shop with quick breakfast and delicious coffee. Great addition to the area.

(Translated by Google) Very reasonable prices for the quality of the dishes and coffees. A pleasant, simple and welcoming service. Highly recommended  (Original) Des prix tres raisonnables pour la qualité des plats et cafés. Un service agréable, simple et accueillant. Très recommandé
Nice staff, excellent coffee!
Great food and coffee!

I’ve been in New York for 15 years, been to so many coffee shops but coffee isn’t as good as boundless plains! It’s not just the espresso drinks but also the amazing and friendly staff not to mention Jo, Julio, Katie and Elise who always start my day with a friendly smile. My fav go-tos are the breakfast sandwiches, tomato toast and oat flat white, must try!! 🥐☕️🖤
They have pretty good coffee and it is really nice and cozy inside.
Absurdly nice staff good coffee nice vibes!

Very new coffee shop. Plenty of space to sit and work from. Its never been too loud when I have visited. The coffee drinks are what you would expect, but the staff is extremely helpful and pleasant. Finally there is another option besides the green mermaid.
By far the best flat white and latte we have had in NYC.  Their avacado toast and crossaints we're beyond amazing! Highly recommend a stop in here if you are in the financial district!
Great neighborhood coffee shop. The coffee is smooth and they have their own brand. Tuna sandwich was also very good and tasty.
Bright and stylish cafe serving an array of specialty espressos drinks and hearty breakfast sandwiches.

I generally look for 3 things in the places I frequent:  Service - the staff here are friendly and welcoming. I'm very happy to be a regular here as they remember things we have talked about previously and ask follow-up questions about things we have previously discussed.  Offering - the coffee is delicious. The food is always fresh. The specials keeps the menu interesting. The presentation is unique and consistent.  Atmosphere - the location is comfortable and clean. Don't let the wire mesh chairs fool you, they are super comfortable.  I hope you found this review helpful.
Very neat and clean environment!!!
Best. Avocado toast. Ever.  It's got like a whole avocado on it.
Very good and strong espresso. Went well with the almond croissant

So glad this place moved in.  Bright atmosphere, good playlist, wonderful employees, and great food and coffee (more on that below).  The owner comes in weekdays and helps take orders and really takes the time to get to know her customers! And the coffee is fantastic--best flat white in the city in my opinion. Avocado toast is also so good. Tons of flavor and definitely not skimpy on the avocado! Can't wait to try out the other menu items!
Only decent coffee in NY
Excellent espresso drinks. Flat white to die for. Great service.
Great coffee! Food is fresh and tasty
The best flat white I've had. Great selection. Extremely friendly staff. Fast and efficient service.
Finally a great place for a coffee and bite in the neighborhood with a relaxing vibe. Love this place for its creative, healthy, and delicious food and drinks.
Great almond milk latte!
Great addition to the neighborhood. Excellent coffee and food.
Terrrible experience. They tell me there is no nuts in an item as I'm allergic but there was almond milk in it..
So excited to have this Australian coffeshop in the neighborhood. The owner is super friendly, and the shop serves great coffees and food. Nice place to sit down, relax and escape the city.
Great coffee
Rally good espresso drinks and offers healthy juices. I haven't tried the food but looked good. Also has seating area.
Awesome space with great vibe, coffee and healthy delicious food.
Stopped in for a large coffee with milk. Good quality coffee.
Just had the Wattle Special and a Matcha Chai it was amazing
